Greta Thunberg was confronted in the hallway of her hotel by right-wing media outlet Rebel News. In a 10-minute video posted to YouTube late Thursday, the Rebel employee asked Thunberg’s associates whether it’s appropriate to exploit a child with a mental illness.
“I don’t have a mental illness,” Thunberg laughed in the video.
The questioner asked whether she’ll disclose who funded her trip to Canada in the middle of a federal election campaign.
“I have not spoken about politics,” Thunberg said.
“Climate change is politics, is it not?” the Rebel employee asked.
“No. It’s science,” Thunberg responded.

user/name: Green Party of Canada | Parti vert du Canada
text:
Greens have the courage to be the first to heed the studies, stand up to the harmful stigma and call for the decriminalization of drugs. 

12 people are dying from drug use in this country every day. 12 human lives, every day. Over 10,000 between 2016 and 2018. We need to declare a national emergency and start saving lives, instead of wagging our fingers and turning our backs. But the leaders in this country are afraid of how the stigma will impact their popularity, and their chances of winning.

We're not doing this because it's popular, we're doing it because it's the right thing to do.

Portugal did it, and results make it clear. Jail, vilification, fear and criminal records don't stop drug addiction, connection stops drug addiction. Community stops drug addiction. It's time to do what people in Canada do best and be there for each other.

This isn’t legalizing drugs, it’s treating addiction as a mental health issue not a crime. We want to boost funding to mental health supports, and community organizations focused on drug testing. 

That's the incredible value of the Green Party: we don't fight for the prime minister's office, we fight for the people who need to be fought for, and force the other parties to answer to us. Addicts are people, and we're standing up for them.

user/name: Conservative Party of Canada - Parti conservateur du Canada
text:
Today, the Conservative Party of Canada released a publicly available social media post by Justin Trudeau’s handpicked candidate for Stormont-Dundas-South Glengarry, Heather Megill.

In a Facebook post dated November 27, 2016, Ms. Megill declared, “Long live the Revolution” in response to the death of Cuban dictator Fidel Castro. Under Castro’s rule, thousands were impoverished, thousands were imprisoned and executed, and free speech, thought and assembly were curtailed or banned.

It is disgusting that Justin Trudeau’s Liberal Party is selecting candidates who call for political violence, the imprisonment of religious and ethnic minorities, and the persecution of the LGBT community.

Trudeau himself praised Fidel Castro as “a legendary revolutionary and orator.” Trudeau also praised Fidel Castro’s “love for the Cuban people” despite the fact that the dictator murdered and imprisoned hundreds of thousands of people.

The Cuban people continue to endure oppression under Fidel Castro’s regime, even after his death. For Justin Trudeau’s candidate to call for further revolution and violence against the Cuban people is reprehensible.

Why do antisemites and people who hold these oppressive views have a home in Justin Trudeau’s Liberal Party?

Heather Megill was acclaimed by Justin Trudeau on September 4, 2019.

user/name: Conservative Party of Canada - Parti conservateur du Canada
text:
Aujourd’hui, le Parti conservateur du Canada a diffusé un message public affiché par la candidate libérale choisie personnellement par Justin Trudeau dans la circonscription de Stormont-Dundas-Sud Glengarry, Heather Megill.

Le 27 novembre 2016, Mme Megill a écrit sur Facebook « Longue vie à la Révolution » en réponse au décès du dictateur cubain Fidel Castro. Le régime de Castro a appauvri des milliers de personnes, a emprisonné et exécuté des milliers de gens, et a restreint ou interdit la liberté d’expression, de pensée et d’assemblée.

Il est répugnant que le Parti libéral de Justin Trudeau choisisse des candidats qui défendent la violence politique, l’emprisonnement de minorités religieuses et ethniques, et la persécution de la communauté LGBT.

Justin Trudeau a lui-même fait l’éloge de Fidel Castro en le décrivant comme « un révolutionnaire et orateur légendaire ». Trudeau a aussi louangé « l’amour de la population cubaine » pour Fidel Castro, même si ce dictateur a assassiné et emprisonné des centaines de milliers de personnes.  

La population cubaine continue de subir l’oppression du régime de Fidel Castro, même après sa mort. Il est répugnant que la candidate de Justin Trudeau défende la révolution et la violence contre la population cubaine.

Pourquoi des antisémites et des personnes qui défendent des régimes oppressifs ont leur place au Parti libéral de Justin Trudeau?

Justin Trudeau a nommé Heather Megill candidate le 4 septembre 2019.

Philippe Gagnon, candidat conservateur dans Jonquière-Haut-Saguenay was born with clubfeet, a malformation that forced him to undergo many surgical procedures before he could take his first steps. 

At around the age of 10, he joined the Chicoutimi Swimming Club, where he developed the skills that would allow him to excel in his sport and overcome the obstacles related to his condition.

 With the encouragement of his family, his determination, hard work, and courage he went to the 2000 Sydney Paralympic Games where he left with 4 paralympic medals. He even held a world record for more than 17 years.
